Vheadline
p2
VTribute to a maestro
p3
sVnews
p4
VDr. Chinna Moulana Memorial Trust in association with the Rasika Ranjana Sabha, Tiruchi, celebrated its tenth anniversary by organising a three-day &#8216;Shraddanjali&#8217; as a tribute to nagaswaram maestro Sheikh Chinna Moulana. A series of concerts were featured as part of the programme.The inaugural day began with Unnikrishnan&#8217;s  vocal concert. Commencing with a composition by Neelakanta Sivan, &#8216;Umaikuriya&#8217; in Pantuvarali, Unnikrishnan presented a series of kirtanas in  his unique style. It was an aural treat for the music lovers when he rendered a couple of Tyagaraja kritis  &#8211; &#8216;Nadhaloludai&#8217; in Kalyana Vasantham and &#8216;Tulasidala&#8217; in Mayamalavagowla ragam. The main piece, &#8216;Avayamba&#8217;  showcased  his outstanding capability in ensuring the precision.An intelligent support by T. V. Ramanujarcharayalu on the violin, Arun Prakash on the mridangam and K. V. Gopalakrishnan on the ganjira was an aural treat for the audience.The nagaswaram concert by Mambalam M.K.S. Siva and party ushered in the Tamil New Year. After a brief alapana of raga Bahudari followed the Thulaseevanam song &#8216;Bhajamanasa.&#8217; Then he rendered the kriti &#8216;Varuvaro Varam Tharuvaaro&#8217; by Gopalakrishna Bharati in  Sama. This was followed by a Tyagaraja kriti &#8216;Devadi Deva&#8217; in  raga Sinduramakriya. Siva  took up  Abheri for elaborate treatment and presented a pallavi set to Adi talam, which was followed by a Ragamalika.  A scintillating tani avartanam on special thavil by Thiruppungur T.G.Muthukumarasamy and Veliyambakkam V.M.Ganapathy followed next. The concert traversed easily with the kritis in Yamuna Kalyani, Maund and Kaapi. The concert ended with the traditional &#8216;Bhagyadha Lakshmi Bharamma.&#8217;Ganesh-Kumaresh (violin)  began  the concert with Sri Raga varnam. A brief alaphana of Mohanam preceded the kriti, &#8216;Rakta Ganapathim&#8217; of Muthuswamy Dikshitar. Then, followed the Darbar raga kriti &#8216;Mundhuvenuka.&#8217;  The kriti, &#8216;Kanden Kalitheerndhen&#8217; of Gopalakrishna Bharati in raga Kalyani was followed by Tyagaraja&#8217;s  &#8216;Vaachama Gocharame&#8217; in Kaikavashi. The matured treatment of the raga Harikhambhodi was outstanding.&#8216;Dhinamani Vamsa&#8217; of Tyagaraja was rendered with grandeur.The tani avartanam by Thanjavur T.R.Govindarajan on thavil and Parupalli Phalgun on mridangam added value to the concert and kept the audience spellbound.Ganesh-Kumaresh (violin) concluded the concert after rending the tradional &#8216;Bhagyadha Lakshmi Bharamma,&#8217;  the Bharatiyar song, &#8216;Paarukkulle Nallanadu&#8217; and a Western note.
